Source: Company data, Morgan Stanley Research
2Q25 profit was largely in line. SIAC's profit remained flat QoQ with soft traffic growth offset by soft commercial spending.
Duty- free revenue and per pax spending continued to drop YoY and QoQ on a low base.
Other commercial revenue such as advertising revenue also dropped YoY amid soft macro.

SIAC reported net profit of Rmb1,044mn in 1H25, tracking 49% of Mse and 47% of consensus. Implied 2Q25 net profit was Rmb525mn up 22% YoY but largely flat QoQ. SIAC also announced an interim dividend of Rmb0.21/share, indicating a 50% payout ratio and 0.6% dividend yield on last close.

- Pax traffic (PVG+SHA) grew 10% YoY in 2Q25, with non-domestic traffic up 19% YoY, recovering to 95% of 2019. 
- Operating costs including SG&A was largely flat YoY in 2Q25, despite traffic growth. 
- OCF was Rmb2.5bn vs. capex of Rmb588mn and lease payment of Rmb974mn, indicating positive FCF

- Commercial revenue grew 2% YoY in 1H25, slower vs. traffic growth. 
- Advertising revenue was down 8% YoY amid soft macro. 
- Duty-free revenue was Rmb285mn in 2Q25 vs. Rmb343mn in 1Q25 and Rmb301mn in 2Q24. We estimate per head DF spending was \(\sim\) Rmb240 in 2Q25, down 21% QoQ and YoY on a low base.
MORGAN STANLEY ASIA LIMITED+
Benny Song Equity Analyst
Teny Song Equity Analyst
Shanghai International Airport (600009.SS, 600009 CG)

DCF, probability- weighted bull \(15\%\) , base \(70\%\) , bear \(15\%\) . We see equal probability that earnings recovery will be better than expected - supported by traffic growth and other commercial revenue - or worse than expected - with further softening of duty- free business. Key assumptions: \(9.0\%\) WACC (1.0x equity beta, \(1.8\%\) risk- free rate, \(8.0\%\) equity risk premium) and \(2\%\) terminal growth rate.
- Stronger-than-expected international travel recovery- Better-than-expected per head commercial spending- Duty-free contract renewal with higher sales commission

- Macro headwinds weighing on air demand- Soft consumption hampering overall commercial spending other than duty-free- Traffic dilution from third airport in Shanghai- Potential capex investment in T3 hampering earnings growth
